pt.runtime

Class ParaTask

  • java.lang.Object
    • pt.runtime.ParaTask

  • public class ParaTask
extends java.lang.Object
    Author:
    Mostafa Mehrabi, Nasser Giacaman, Oliver Sinnen

    Helper methods for the ParaTask runtime. This class contains various functions to set up the ParaTask runtime. Importantly the type of scheduling, thread pool type, thread pool size, the EDT and the task listener are set and retrieved via this class.

    All applications making use of the ParaTask features should invoke init() early in the main method. This will initialise various aspects of the ParaTask runtime.

      • setThreadPoolSize

        public static boolean setThreadPoolSize(ParaTask.ThreadPoolType threadPoolType,
                                        int size)
        Set the size of the thread pool. To have any effect, this must be executed very early before ParaTask creates the runtime. This method throws IllegalArgumentException if the parameter passed to it is smaller than one. This method returns false if it fails to adjust thread pool. This happens when ParaTask has already started working (i.e., TaskInfos are enqueued and TaskIDs are created), otherwise it returns true
        Parameters:
        size -
        Returns:
        boolean true if scheduling type is changed successfully, otherwise false.

      • setSchedulingType

        public static boolean setSchedulingType(ParaTask.ScheduleType type)
        Set the scheduling scheme. This only has an effect if no tasks have been executed yet (i.e. must be called before ParaTask is initialized). This method throws IllegalAccessExecption if ParaTask is initialized earlier. This method returns false if it fails to adjust thread pool. This happens when ParaTask has already started working (i.e., TaskInfos are enqueued and TaskIDs are created), otherwise it returns true
        Parameters:
        type - The schedule to use.
        Returns:
        boolean true if scheduling type is changed successfully, otherwise false.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalAccessException

        public static int activeInteractiveTaskCount()
        Returns a count of the number of active interactive tasks. Useful if need to decide whether a task should be invoked interactively or not (e.g. to limit thread count).
        Returns:
        The number of active interactive tasks.

      • init

        public static boolean init()
        To be executed by the main thread (i.e. inside the main method). Registers the main thread and event dispatch thread with ParaTask, and instantiates a task pool with the default WorkStealing scheduling policy, iff the scheduling policy is not set by the used beforehand. Otherwise, it initialized the task pool using the user-specified scheduling policy.
        Returns:
        boolean If ParaTask has not been initialized before, this method returns true once the setup is done. Otherwise (i.e., ParaTask has been initialized before) it returns false.
        Since:
        2015
